	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have found that PAL controllers (model NES-004E) will work universally on both the PAL and NTSC NES, but the NTSC controllers (model NES-004) only work with the NTSC NES. You can make an NTSC controller 'PAL-compatible' by adding two resistors - more details here:<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.made-by-bacteria.com/viewtopic.php?f=30&amp;t=1199">http://www.made-by-bacteria.com/viewtop ... =30&amp;t=1199</a><!-- m --><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://retro.mmgn.com/NES/Forums/Nes-Controller-NTSC-to-PAL-Conversion">http://retro.mmgn.com/NES/Forums/Nes-Co ... Conversion</a><!-- m -->

		

